'''Finnish Nature Heritage Foundation''' is a foundation founded in 1995 by Finnish ecological activist [[Pentti Linkola]]. It has founded to preserve the remaining [[old-growth forest]]s. The foundation gets donations from private individuals and companies, and then buys the forest areas seemed unique enough to deserve the protection. The protection of forests is double guaranteed - the forests are protected by Finnish nature protection laws, but also by being legally in ownership of Finnish Nature Heritage Foundation.

