{{Infobox oil field | name = Shmidtivske | country = [[Ukraine]] | region = [[Black Sea]] | location = | block = | offonshore = offshore | coordinates = | operator = | operators = | partners = [[Chornomornaftogaz]] | contractors = | image = | caption = | discovery = 1979 | start_development = 1979 | start_production = 1979 | abandonment = | peak_year = | peak_of_production_oil_bbl/d = | peak_of_production_oil_tpy = | peak_of_production_gas_mmcuft/d = | peak_of_production_gas_mmscm/d = | peak_of_production_gas_bcm/y = | oil_production_bbl/d = | oil_production_tpy = | production_year_oil = | production_gas_mmcuft/d = 40 | production_gas_mmscm/d = 1 | production_gas_bcm/y = 0.3 | production_year_gas = | est_oil_bbl = | est_oil_t = | recover_oil_bbl = | recover_oil_t = | est_gas_bft = 565 | est_gas_bcm = 16 | recover_gas_bft = | recover_gas_bcm = | formations = }}
The '''Shmidtivske gas field''' [[natural gas field]] located on the continental shelf of the [[Black Sea]]. It was discovered in 1974 and developed by [[Chornomornaftogaz]]. It started commercial production in 1975. The total [[proven reserves]] of the Shmidtivske gas field are around {{convert|565|e9cuft}}, and production is slated to be around {{convert|40|e6cuft/d}} in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.geoecomar.ro/website/publicatii/Nr.3-1998/3.VasylISozansky.pdf|title=Ukrainian Black Sea gas fields|date=2009|publisher=geoecomar.ro|accessdate=2014-03-27}}</ref>
